"{\"uid\": \"tsn.ca-olympics-noah-lyles-wins-olympic-100-meter-final-by-excruciating-close-margin-1.2158100\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Published:August 04, 2024 at 2:41PM EDT  SAINT-DENIS, France (AP) - Noah Lyles paced on the far end of the track, hands folded over the top of his head, wistfully looking up at a scoreboard that would, sooner or later, flash an answer he's been seeking over three sweat-soaked years.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 41, \"end\": 52, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.993648926404979e-12, \"text\": \"SAINT-DENIS\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 54, \"end\": 60, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999479785386198, \"rank\": 5.196548158919434e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.2301771847634596e-12, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was all that toil since the last Olympics - all the work on the practice track and in the weight room in the name of finding a centimeter here or a millisecond there - really going to be worth all the trouble?\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ten seconds passed, then 20.\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 524, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, nearly 30.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And then, the answer popped up.\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 573, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, Lyles is the 100-meter champion at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 580, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The World's Fastest Man.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just not by very much.\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The American showman edged out Jamaica's Kishane Thompson on Sunday by five-thousandths of a second - that's .005 of one tick of the clock - in a race for the ages.\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9990349811682327, \"rank\": 0.0009538389176880593, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.9136298468299497e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 734, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9994585873094793, \"rank\": 0.000541705976980802, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The final tally in this one: Lyles 9.784 seconds, Thompson 9.789.\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 916, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new champion said that before he left for Paris, one of his physio guys ensured him this race would be a squeaker.\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5454203655647467e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He said, 'This is how close first and second are going to be,'\\\" Lyles said as he pinched his thumb and his forefinger together so they were almost touching.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I can not believe how right he was.\\\"\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For perspective, the blink of an eye takes, on average, .1 second.\", \"from\": 1235, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That was 20 times longer than the gap between first and second.\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was so close, that when the sprinters crossed the line and the word \\\"Photo\\\" popped up next to the names of Lyles, Thompson and five others in the eight-man field, Lyles walked over to the Jamaican and said \\\"I think you got the Olympics dog.\\\"\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1477, \"end\": 1482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1484, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9994585873094793, \"rank\": 0.000541705976980802, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 1558, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.8047906836614217, \"rank\": 0.24255911543197536, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson, who raced three lanes to the left of Lyles and had no clue where he was on the track, wasn't convinced.\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1726, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9994585873094793, \"rank\": 0.000541705976980802, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1660, \"end\": 1665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was, 'Wow, I am not even sure, because it was that close,'\\\" the Jamaican said.\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1809, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1795, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.8047906836614217, \"rank\": 0.24255911543197536, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Time would tell.\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It always does.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When Lyles' name came up first, he snatched his name tag off the front of his bib and held it to the sky.\", \"from\": 1844, \"to\": 1949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moments later, he shouted at the TV camera: \\\"America, I told you I got this!\\\"\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The first four racers were separated by less than .03.\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top seven all finished within .09 of each other.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"America's Fred Kerley came in third at 9.81.\", \"from\": 2138, \"to\": 2182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2148, \"end\": 2159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Kerley\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Kerley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's probably one of the most beautiful races I have been in,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2257, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the photo finish, Kerley's orange shoe crossed the line before anyone, or anything.\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's the chest breaking the barrier that counts.\", \"from\": 2346, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles' chest crossed first.\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the closest 1-2 finish in the 100 since at least Moscow in 1980 - or maybe even ever.\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2486, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4107094937665136e-14, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back then, Britain's Allan Wells narrowly beat Silvio Leonard in an era when the electronic timers did not go into the thousandths of a second.\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9982411570977016, \"rank\": 0.0017619300937497474, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Allan Wells\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Allan_Wells\"}, {\"begin\": 2571, \"end\": 2585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Silvio Leonard\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silvio_Leonard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same was true in 1932, when Eddie Tolan won the Olympics' first ever photo finish.\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eddie Tolan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddie_Tolan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles conceded that during the excruciating wait, he was pretty sure he had dipped his chest just a tad too soon.\", \"from\": 2756, \"to\": 2869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dipping, it turns out, is one of the few things he does not work on over and over again at his training track in Florida.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2983, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"score\": 0.797080390638658, \"rank\": 0.2539687643228627, \"text\": \"Florida\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Florida\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I would say I have a decent history with dipping,\\\" he said, recalling races he won in high school and as a junior.\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 9.784 marked a new personal best for Lyles and made him the first American champion in the marquee race at the Olympics since Justin Gatlin in 2004.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3155, \"end\": 3160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 3244, \"end\": 3257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Justin Gatlin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Justin_Gatlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles is hoping to go even bigger than that, and maybe take this sport back to a day when it was Carl Lewis and Edwin Moses lighting up the track - a must-see affair, the likes of which Lyles headlined in front of around 80,000 on a warm night at the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Lewis\"}, {\"begin\": 3380, \"end\": 3391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Edwin Moses\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Edwin_Moses\"}, {\"begin\": 3454, \"end\": 3459, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 3519, \"end\": 3534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mission started after Lyles settled for a bronze medal in Tokyo in his favorite - and then, only - sprint, the 200.\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 3599, \"end\": 3604, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999891620065, \"rank\": 1.0713801533986599e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those COVID-impacted Games were a terrible experience for Lyles.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3715, \"end\": 3720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He rededicated himself to bettering his mental health, but also looked for a new mission - the 100 meters and, with it, a chance at track immortality.\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice was tough for a sprinter never known as a great starter, but he stuck with it.\", \"from\": 3874, \"to\": 3965, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When he won the world championships last year, then backed it up by winning the 200, his goal for Paris was very much in sight.\", \"from\": 3966, \"to\": 4093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4064, \"end\": 4069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5454203655647467e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when he came into the Olympic final having finished second in both his qualifying races and staring across at one sprinter who had run faster than him this year - Thompson - and another who had beaten him twice this year - Jamaica's Oblique Seville - he knew this would be no coronation.\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4322, \"end\": 4329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.9136298468299497e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 4340, \"end\": 4347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0313448743718235e-13, \"text\": \"Seville\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seville\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Thompson added another roadblock when, during the introduction, he let out a primal scream, the likes of which Lyles has been unleashing in some of his biggest races.\", \"from\": 4388, \"to\": 4554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4388, \"end\": 4396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9994585873094793, \"rank\": 0.000541705976980802, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Klay_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 4499, \"end\": 4504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought 'Man, that's my thing, that's crazy,'\\\" Lyles said.\", \"from\": 4556, \"to\": 4617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles galloped and leapt about 20 yards down the track before returning to the starting line, where the runners waited some three minutes for the gun to finally sound.\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was worth the wait.\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, the question that could be debated for years is: What was the difference in this one?\", \"from\": 4812, \"to\": 4902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Could it have been Lyles' closing speed and that lean into the line that he thought was mistimed?\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 5001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4923, \"end\": 4928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"score\": 0.9962146911447616, \"rank\": 0.003799540493677415, \"text\": \"Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was it his ability to stay in reach of everyone among this straight line of sprinters over the first 60 meters - a skill he's been working on in tedious practice after practice since he took on the shorter sprint?\", \"from\": 5003, \"to\": 5216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer: all that and more.\", \"from\": 5218, \"to\": 5248, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Everyone in the field came out knowing they could win this race,\\\" Lyles said.\", \"from\": 5250, \"to\": 5328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took 9.784 seconds, then about 30 seconds more, for the scoreboard to flash the name of the man who actually did.\", \"from\": 5330, \"to\": 5446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Seeing that name, I was like 'Oh my gosh, there it is!'\\\"\", \"from\": 5448, \"to\": 5505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles said.\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5517, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold (and bronze) for Ukrainian high jumpers  Yaroslava Mahuchikh won Olympic gold in the high jump for her war-torn country of Ukraine and, as a bonus, had company.\", \"from\": 5519, \"to\": 5684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5541, \"end\": 5550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9993266982329488, \"rank\": 0.0006338039435036215, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 5565, \"end\": 5584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yaroslava Mahuchikh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yaroslava_Mahuchikh\"}, {\"begin\": 5647, \"end\": 5654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9575995907440189, \"rank\": 0.044268873171726585, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her teammate Iryna Gerashchenko won the bronze and the teammates hopped, skipped and jumped around the track parading their blue-and-yellow flags in a heartfelt celebration.\", \"from\": 5685, \"to\": 5858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5704, \"end\": 5716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"score\": 0.9951516416830872, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerashchenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mahuchikh needed fewer tries to clear the winning height of 2 meters than Australia's Nicola Olyslagers, and so, added the sport's biggest prize of all - Olympic gold - to her world championship and world record.\", \"from\": 5860, \"to\": 6072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5934, \"end\": 5943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.9999694803746744, \"rank\": 2.845330553363282e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5946, \"end\": 5952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9999976394488507, \"rank\": 2.3605555723088563e-06, \"text\": \"Nicola\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicola_Roberts\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kerr vs Ingebrigtsen is a go for heated men's 1,500  The best rivalry in track will culminate Tuesday when reigning world champion Josh Kerr of Britain takes on defending Olympic champion Jakob Ingebrigtsen of Norway.\", \"from\": 6074, \"to\": 6291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6205, \"end\": 6209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"score\": 0.9999131644191299, \"rank\": 7.400403232355001e-05, \"text\": \"Josh\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Josh_Madden\"}, {\"begin\": 6218, \"end\": 6225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9982411570977016, \"rank\": 0.0017619300937497474, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 6262, \"end\": 6280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 6284, \"end\": 6290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9884902004240984, \"rank\": 0.011585198506653092, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They squared off in Sunday's semifinal, too, and Ingebrigtsen edged out the Brit, looking over to him twice as they surged down the homestretch, to win a race that felt like it meant more than it should have in 3:32.38.\", \"from\": 6293, \"to\": 6512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They should be expecting one of the most vicious and hardest 1,500s the sport's seen in a very long time,\\\" Kerr said.\", \"from\": 6514, \"to\": 6632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Did Ingebrigtsen agree?\", \"from\": 6634, \"to\": 6657, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Depends who you ask, maybe,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 6659, \"to\": 6697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I mean, racing is what you want it to be.\\\"\", \"from\": 6698, \"to\": 6741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"___  AP Summer Olympics: https://apnews.com/hub/2024-paris-olympic-games  \\u00a92025 BellMedia All Rights Reserved\", \"from\": 6743, \"to\": 6852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6748, \"end\": 6750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.2301771847634596e-12, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}]}"